Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the tomatoes to the bowl of dressing and set aside for later.

In a small bowl, combine the @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}, @mayonnaise{64%grams},
@honey{15%grams} and @water{1%tbsp} for the sauce.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your hot honey 'Nduja mayo aside.

When the chips have about ~{10%minutes} remaining, place the
@ready to eat falafels{171%grams} onto a lined baking tray and bake on the middle
shelf until golden brown, ~{5-8%minutes}.

A couple mins before the falafels are ready, pop your @plain taco tortillas{4}
into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Just before everything's ready, toss the baby gem with the tomatoes and dressing.

To make your wraps, lay the tortillas on your plates.

Top with the falafels and some of the salad. Drizzle over the hot honey 'Nduja mayo
and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams}. Sprinkle the
@crispy onions{1%sachet} over to finish and fold in the sides of the tortillas to
make your wraps.

Serve with the chips and any remaining salad on the side. Enjoy!